# =============================================================================
# Dynamic Media Card Tool — Environment Configuration
# =============================================================================
#
# IMPORTANT: X Ads API ONLY supports OAuth 1.0a user context.
# X API v2 supports both, but we use OAuth 1.0a for the whole flow so that
# the same tokens that let users sign in can also call the Ads API.
#
# The web app lets OTHER USERS sign in with their X account ("Sign in with X")
# and authorize this App. Their OAuth1 tokens are stored and used when they
# operate on *their own* Ads accounts.
#
# =============================================================================
# 1. X_CONSUMER_KEY and X_CONSUMER_SECRET (REQUIRED for Ads API)
# =============================================================================
# These are the "Consumer Keys" / "API Key & Secret" (OAuth 1.0a).
#
# How to get them:
#   1. Go to https://developer.x.com
#   2. Open (or create) your App
#   3. Go to the "Keys and tokens" tab
#   4. Under "Consumer Keys", generate / copy:
#        - API Key            → X_CONSUMER_KEY
#        - API Key Secret     → X_CONSUMER_SECRET
#
#   5. Also configure OAuth 1.0a settings:
#        - Enable OAuth 1.0a
#        - App permissions: "Read and Write" (recommended)
#        - Callback URL(s): register EXACTLY the same value you will use for X_REDIRECT_URI
#          (e.g. http://127.0.0.1:8000/callback or your production URL)
#
# After a user clicks "Sign in with X", they go through the classic 3-legged OAuth1 flow
# and we receive oauth_token + oauth_token_secret that work for Ads API calls.
#
# =============================================================================
# 2. X_REDIRECT_URI (required)
# =============================================================================
# Must exactly match a registered Callback URL for OAuth 1.0a (and OAuth 2.0 if used).
# Local example:
X_REDIRECT_URI=http://127.0.0.1:8000/callback
#
# Production:
# X_REDIRECT_URI=https://your-app.onrender.com/callback

X_CONSUMER_KEY=your-consumer-key-here
X_CONSUMER_SECRET=your-consumer-secret-here

# (Optional) OAuth 2.0 Client ID/Secret — only needed if you want to keep a legacy path.
# Not required for Ads functionality.
# X_CLIENT_ID=
# X_CLIENT_SECRET=

# =============================================================================
# 3. SECRET_KEY (required for sessions + token encryption)
# =============================================================================
# Generate a strong random value. Never commit the real one.
# Good ways to generate:
#   - macOS / Linux:   openssl rand -hex 32
#   - Python:          python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_hex(32))"
#
# For local testing you can use a long dummy, but change it before any real use.
SECRET_KEY=replace-with-a-long-random-string-at-least-32-characters

# =============================================================================
# 4. (Optional) OAUTHLIB_INSECURE_TRANSPORT
# =============================================================================
# Only for local development over plain http://127.0.0.1
# Leave commented out in production (https is required for real OAuth).
# OAUTHLIB_INSECURE_TRANSPORT=1

# =============================================================================
# Notes for Render / other deploys
# =============================================================================
# - Use the exact same variables above.
# - Set X_REDIRECT_URI to your production callback URL (https://.../callback)
# - The app has no database — schedules and tokens are in-memory only.
#   They disappear when the service restarts (normal on free Render).
# - Make sure your X App/Project has the "Ads API" product enabled,
#   otherwise the Ads account and card endpoints will return 403.
